My first attempt on use https://github.com/lycheeverse/lychee-action to automatically create an issue reporting all bad links. Here's an example of that issue: https://github.com/micalevisk/coding-interview-university/issues/1 This issue will be created only if there's some bad link on `README.md` file or in any `.md` on `translations` dir

Besides that, this workflow will find the last open issue with the label 'report' and update it instead of creating a new one. Or will close it if there's no bad link found.

Not sure if you guys are looking for something like this, tho.

Hi there 😄 Thanks for putting together this great guide! I look forward to diving into it personally.

I noticed while reviewing the `README.md` that there are still references to the `master` branch, despite it having been renamed to `main` in this repository (and some others of yours that are also mentioned in the guide). This PR corrects both instructions (such as `git rebase jwasham/master`) and links that still reference the old branch name. I left links which reference `master` in other repositories (either forks of this repo, or your personal `practice-*` repos) that aren't yet updated to use `main`.

I hope this helps, please let me know if I did everything alright! Thanks.
